# =============================================================================
# Phase B — Local env layout (Vercel ↔ machine)
# =============================================================================
# • Pull from Vercel (gitignored):  npm run env:pull   →  .env.vercel
# • Overrides / machine-only:       .env.local         (never commit; *.local is ignored)
# • Merge order: .env.vercel first, then .env.local wins on duplicate keys.
# • Vite (npm run dev): vite.config merges those for VITE_* client vars.
# • Vercel dev + API routes:        npm run dev:vercel  (loads .env.vercel + .env.local)
# • Vercel CLI reference + add commands: docs/vercel-env-setup.md
#
# Variable tags:
#   [vercel]  — store on Vercel (included in `vercel env pull` for the env you pull).
#   [local]   — usually only in .env.local (override, experiment, or not worth syncing).
#   [both]    — typical pattern: value on Vercel + optional .env.local override for dev.
# =============================================================================

# Copy to .env.local and fill in from Supabase → Project Settings → API
# Never commit .env.local (ignored via *.local)

# [both] SEO: canonical https origin, no trailing slash (update public/robots.txt + sitemap.xml if you use a custom domain)
# VITE_SITE_URL=https://quni-living.vercel.app
# [vercel] Optional default Open Graph image (absolute URL, e.g. 1200×630 JPG)
# VITE_OG_IMAGE_URL=

# [vercel] Supabase (same values as dashboard → Project Settings → API)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# [vercel] Publishable key only (sb_publishable_… or legacy anon JWT eyJ…). NEVER sb_secret_… or service_role.
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_publishable_key_here

# [vercel] Public forms (contact, listing enquiry, landlord partnerships) use Resend from Vercel routes:
#   /api/contact, /api/enquiry-email, /api/landlord-lead-email — requires RESEND_API_KEY, TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY,
#   and VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY (see below).

# [vercel] Cloudflare Turnstile (enquiry + booking forms) — https://dash.cloudflare.com/ → Turnstile
# VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
# [vercel] Server secret (not VITE_): TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=
# [both] Optional local dev: point verify to a deployed API
# VITE_TURNSTILE_VERIFY_URL=https://your-app.vercel.app/api/verify-turnstile

# [vercel] Stripe (Payment Element / future checkout — publishable key only in Vite)
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
#
# [vercel] Sentry browser SDK (optional)
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
#
# --- Server-only on Vercel; never use VITE_ prefix for these. See docs/vercel-env-setup.md ---
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_… or sk_live_…
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_…
#   SUPABASE_URL=same URL as VITE_SUPABASE_URL (no VITE_ prefix)
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=service_role JWT from Supabase → API (secret). MUST NOT be the
#     same as anon/publishable — if you paste anon here, Stripe Connect saves 0 rows and
#     stripe_connect_account_id stays NULL with no obvious error.
#   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=EXACT same value as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (publishable/anon key)
#     Required for /api/create-connect-account-link to verify the user JWT.
#     If you only set VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in Vercel, the API uses that too (no duplicate needed).
#   RESEND_API_KEY=re_...  (booking notification emails — Resend dashboard → API Keys)
#   Also set RESEND_API_KEY as a Supabase secret for Edge Functions send-uni-otp (uni email verification).
#   Student account deletion + storage safety net:
#   DELETE_USER_DOCS_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<long random> — must match HTTP header x-webhook-secret on the
#     Database Webhook that calls delete-user-documents (see supabase/README.md).
# Optional: SITE_URL or PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-production-domain.com
# Absolute /api URLs: code falls back to VERCEL_URL — set automatically on Vercel (do not add manually).
#
# Anthropic (AI — /api/ai/generate-description, /api/ai/student-assessment)
# student-assessment also requires Authorization: Bearer <Supabase access_token> and the same
# SUPABASE_* vars as other authenticated API routes (see above).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# [vercel] OpenAI — text embeddings for AI chat RAG (text-embedding-3-small). Server-only.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# [vercel] Quni Living AI Chat (rate limiting + context sizing for `/api/chat`)
CHAT_LIMIT_LOGGED_IN_PER_24H=40
CHAT_LIMIT_VISITOR_PER_HOUR=5
CHAT_LISTING_CONTEXT_MAX_IDS=8
CHAT_MAX_TOKENS=1024

# [vercel] DocuSeal (self-hosted lease signing — sign.quni.com.au)
# DOCUSEAL_API_URL=https://sign.quni.com.au
# DOCUSEAL_API_TOKEN=
# Optional if your instance uses a different path than /api/submissions/pdf:
# DOCUSEAL_SUBMISSIONS_PATH=/api/submissions/pdf
#
# Internal trigger from booking confirmation → POST /api/documents/generate-lease
# INTERNAL_DOC_FLOW_SECRET= (generate a long random string; same value in Vercel)
#
# If the project uses Vercel Deployment Protection (login wall on previews/production), enable
# “Protection Bypass for Automation” in Vercel → Project → Settings → Deployment Protection.
# Vercel injects VERCEL_AUTOMATION_BYPASS_SECRET; server-to-server fetch to your own /api/* routes
# must send header x-vercel-protection-bypass (create-rent-subscription does this automatically).

# For local API routes: npm run env:pull, then npm run dev:vercel
# (or put the same keys in .env.local and run npx vercel dev).
